/**
@class cv::vcucodec::Encoder
@brief VCU Encoder interface for encoding video streams

The VCU Encoder provides hardware-accelerated video encoding on AMD/Xilinx Versal and
Zynq UltraScale+ MPSoC platforms.

Supported codecs:
- AVC/H.264
- HEVC/H.265

Features include:
- Multiple rate control modes (CBR, VBR, Constant QP, etc.)
- HDR SEI support
- Dynamic parameter adjustment
- GOP configuration

Use @ref cv::vcucodec::createEncoder "createEncoder" to create an instance.

@anchor enc_fourcc_table
Supported input FOURCC codes (set via
@ref cv::vcucodec::PictureEncSettings::fourcc "PictureEncSettings::fourcc"):

| FOURCC | Format | Bit Depth | Chroma | Notes |
|--------|--------|-----------|--------|-------|
| Y800   | Monochrome | 8-bit | 4:0:0 | Grayscale |
| Y010   | Monochrome | 10-bit | 4:0:0 | Grayscale |
| Y012   | Monochrome | 12-bit | 4:0:0 | VCU2 only |
| NV12   | YUV | 8-bit | 4:2:0 | Semi-planar (Y + interleaved UV) |
| P010   | YUV | 10-bit | 4:2:0 | Semi-planar |
| P012   | YUV | 12-bit | 4:2:0 | VCU2 only |
| NV16   | YUV | 8-bit | 4:2:2 | Semi-planar |
| P210   | YUV | 10-bit | 4:2:2 | Semi-planar |
| P212   | YUV | 12-bit | 4:2:2 | VCU2 only |
| I444   | YUV | 8-bit | 4:4:4 | VCU2 only |
| I4AL   | YUV | 10-bit | 4:4:4 | VCU2 only |
| I4CL   | YUV | 12-bit | 4:4:4 | VCU2 only |

### Feeding frames

Two mutually exclusive methods are available for providing input to the encoder:

- @ref cv::vcucodec::Encoder::write "write(frame)" — Encode a single cv::Mat frame. The frame
  must match the FourCC and dimensions specified in PictureEncSettings. Call repeatedly for each
  frame, then call eos() to finalize.

- @ref cv::vcucodec::Encoder::writeFile "writeFile(filename, startFrame, numFrames, picSettings)"
  — Read and encode frames directly from a RAW YUV file on disk.
  Parameters:
  - @p filename — Path to a RAW YUV file (no container, just packed pixel data).
  - @p startFrame — 0-based frame index to start encoding from (default: 0).
  - @p numFrames — Number of frames to encode; 0 encodes all frames until EOF (default: 0).
  - @p picSettings — Optional per-file PictureEncSettings to override resolution
    (must be <= the initial resolution).

  writeFile() can be called multiple times with different files before calling eos().

After all frames have been submitted (via either method), call
@ref cv::vcucodec::Encoder::eos "eos()" to signal end-of-stream and wait for the encoder to
flush its pipeline.



### Properties

Properties can be queried via @ref cv::vcucodec::Encoder::get "get(propId)" and set via
@ref cv::vcucodec::Encoder::set "set(propId, value)":

| Property | get | set | Description |
|----------|-----|-----|-------------|
| CAP_PROP_FOURCC | ✓ | | Codec type (H264, HEVC, MJPG) |
| CAP_PROP_CODEC_PIXEL_FORMAT | ✓ | | Input pixel format FOURCC (e.g. NV12) |
| CAP_PROP_FRAME_WIDTH | ✓ | | Width of the picture in pixels |
| CAP_PROP_FRAME_HEIGHT | ✓ | | Height of the picture in pixels |
| CAP_PROP_FPS | ✓ | ✓ | Framerate of the encoding session |
| CAP_PROP_BITRATE | ✓ | ✓ | Target bitrate in kbits per second |
| CAP_PROP_POS_FRAMES | ✓ | | Number of frames encoded so far |
| CAP_PROP_POS_MSEC | ✓ | | Current position in milliseconds |

@note Setting properties via set(propId, value) updates cached settings only.
Use the dynamic commands (@ref cv::vcucodec::Encoder::setFrameRate "setFrameRate()",
@ref cv::vcucodec::Encoder::setBitRate "setBitRate()") to change parameters mid-stream.

Additional information methods:
- @ref cv::vcucodec::Encoder::settings "settings()" — returns a multi-line string with all
  current encoder settings (picture, rate control, GOP, profile, slice, GMV).
- @ref cv::vcucodec::Encoder::statistics "statistics()" — returns a string with encoding
  performance: number of pictures encoded and average frame rate (fps).

See @ref enc_python_examples_anchor "Encoder Python Examples" for usage examples.
*/
